FileScanner follows imports starting from main.drift.xml, parses each .drift.xml as XML, extracts spec elements with their id attribute, processes inner content to extract spec-spec edges (recording each &lt;ref spec="…"&gt; as an Edge with From = the containing spec's module-qualified ID and To = the referenced ID), SHA1-hashes the canonical content (refs stripped, label text preserved), and returns Spec records with module-qualified ID, Hash, Filepath, and LineNumber alongside the discovered spec-spec Edges. See principles.language_agnostic.